sec.p:
The amphipod genus Ceradocus was established by Costa (1853)
with C . orchestiipesCosta , 1853
as its type species. Sheard (1939) revised Australian Ceradocus species and established two subgenera, Ceradocus and DenticeradocusSheard, 1939 , but J.L. Barnard and C.M. Barnard (1983) synonymized these subgenera with the genus. Krapp-Schickel & Vader (2009) enumerated 31 species and two subspecies in the genus and provided a key to the species and subspecies. Afterwards 11 species of the genus have been hitherto added (
Alves et al. 2019
; Dang & Le 2011 ; Hughes 2016 ;
Lim et al. 2010
; Milne & Griffiths 2013 ; Myers & Nithyanandan 2016 ; Ren 2012 ; Wongkamhaeng & Boonyanusith 2016 ;
Wongkamhaeng et al. 2013
).

In the present paper, terms of the teeth on the pleonites and urosomites are defined as follows: dorsal teeth: teeth on the dorsal–dorsolateral posterior margin; posteroventral tooth: tooth on the posteroventral corner of the pleonal epimeron; posterior teeth: teeth on the posterior margin of the epimeron above the posteroventral tooth; ventral teeth: teeth on the ventral margin of the epimeron anterior to the posteroventral tooth. Abbreviations used in the figures and tables are: A, antenna; C, coxa; E, pleonal epimeron; F, female; G, gnathopod; 
GI
, gill

; 
